4f7f43ba3d92d06b363c8405fdb15 "><div class=3D"avia_textblock"><p>In IPv4, s=
ubnet masks, often shown in dot-decimal notation, distinguish the network n=
umber from the host identifier. IPv6 uses the network prefix similarly, wit=
h prefix length indicating the number of address bits.</p><p>Before CIDR, I=
Pv4 network prefixes were derived from the IP address class (A, B, or C) an=
d network mask. Now, IP address assignment requires both an address and its=
 network mask, reflecting modern advancements in network architecture.</p><=
